In C++, a foreach loop is a foor loop, with somthing special. you can make a for each loop with for (typeofarray element : arrayname) { //thiscode will run for every item in the  array }
Grids are arrays of arrays. you define grids with datatype name[sizeofouterarray(rows)][sizeofinnerarray(columns)] = {{values},{values}...};

Our CBit OS devs realized that there can be nested directorys, so the need you to fix the bug. Iterate thorugh the nested array(grid) homeDir and print every element. _You may need to use multiple foreach loops. You can use auto before element : array to make it auto select datatype_

